PrecisOrder confirming that some 38.9 hectares of land situated in the Township of Les Escoumins, Quebec, that were acquired by the Government of Canada in 1892, are a reserve set apart for the use and benefit of the MONTAGNAIS OF LES ESCOUMINS BAND OF INDIANS which is to be known as Les Escoumins Indian Reserve. (Lot A-1, C.L.S.R. Plan 4706)
